apexpages.name: ApexPages
apexpages.description: The ApexPages namespace provides classes used in Visualforce controllers.

applauncher.name: AppLauncher
applauncher.description: The AppLauncher namespace provides methods for managing the appearance of apps in the App Launcher, including their visibility and sort order.

approval.name: Approval
approval.description: The Approval namespace provides classes and methods for approval processes.

auth.name: Auth
auth.description: The Auth namespace provides an interface and classes for single sign-on into Salesforce and session security management.

cache.name: Cache
cache.description: The Cache namespace contains methods for managing the platform cache.

canvas.name: Canvas
canvas.description: The Cache namespace contains methods for managing the platform cache.

chatteranswers.name: ChatterAnswers
chatteranswers.description: The Canvas namespace provides an interface and classes for canvas apps in Salesforce.

commercepayments.name: commercepayments
commercepayments.description: Use the commercepayments namespace to provide a safe and customizable platform for managing customer payments and refunds

connectapi.name: ConnectApi
connectapi.description: The ConnectApi namespace (also called Chatter in Apex) provides classes for accessing the same data available in Chatter REST API. Use Chatter in Apex to create custom Chatter experiences in Salesforce.

database.name: Database
database.description: The Database namespace provides classes used with DML operations.

datacloud.name: Datacloud
datacloud.description: The Datacloud namespace provides classes and methods for retrieving information about duplicate rules. Duplicate rules let you control whether and when users can save duplicate records within Salesforce.

datasource.name: DataSource
datasource.description: The DataSource namespace provides the classes for the Apex Connector Framework. Use the Apex Connector Framework to develop a custom adapter for Salesforce Connect. Then connect your Salesforce organization to any data anywhere via the Salesforce Connect custom adapter.

dom.name: Dom
dom.description: The Dom namespace provides classes and methods for parsing and creating XML content.

eventbus.name: EventBus
eventbus.description: The EventBus namespace provides classes and methods for platform events and Change Data Capture events.

flow.name: Flow
flow.description: The Flow namespace provides a class for advanced Visualforce controller access to flows.

kbmanagement.name: KbManagement
kbmanagement.description: The KbManagement namespace provides a class for managing knowledge articles.

messaging.name: Messaging
messaging.description: The Messaging namespace provides classes and methods for Salesforce outbound and inbound email functionality.

metadata.name: Metadata
metadata.description: The Metadata namespace provides classes and methods for working with custom metadata in Salesforce

process.name: Process
process.description: The Process namespace provides an interface and classes for passing data between your organization and a flow.

quickAction.name: QuickAction
quickAction.description: The QuickAction namespace provides classes and methods for quick actions.

reports.name: Reports
reports.description: The Reports namespace provides classes for accessing the same data as is available in the Salesforce Reports and Dashboards REST API.

schema.name: Schema
schema.description: The Schema namespace provides classes and methods for schema metadata information.

search.name: Search
search.description: The Search namespace provides classes for getting search results and suggestion results.

sfc.name: Sfc
sfc.description: The Sfc namespace contains classes used in Salesforce Files.

site.name: Site
site.description: The Site namespace provides an interface for rewriting Sites URLs.

support.name: Support
support.description: The Support namespace provides an interface used for Case Feed.

system.name: System
system.description: The System namespace provides classes and methods for core Apex functionality

territorymgmt.name: TerritoryMgmt
territorymgmt.description: The TerritoryMgmt namespace provides an interface used for territory management.

txnsecurity.name: TxnSecurity
txnsecurity.description: The TxnSecurity namespace provides an interface used for transaction security.

userprovisioning.name: UserProvisioning
userprovisioning.description: The UserProvisioning namespace provides methods for monitoring outbound user provisioning requests.

visualeditor.name: VisualEditor
visualeditor.description: The VisualEditor namespace provides classes and methods for interacting with the Lightning App Builder. The classes and methods in this namespace operate on Lightning components, which include Lightning web components and Aura components.

wave.name: wave
wave.description: The classes in the wave namespace are part of the Wave Analytics SDK, designed to facilitate querying Wave data from Apex code.
